Trade union federation Cosatu is accusing business leaders of failing to fulfil their promises. JOHANNESBURG - It's only the first month of the year, and already several companies have announced plans to shed jobs despite pledges made at the jobs summit. READ: Cosatu: Retrenchments not justified Trade union federation Cosatu is accusing business leaders of failing to fulfil their promises. It says it wants to discuss the issue with business representatives and the President. READ: ConCourt rules on retrenchment negotiations Business Leadership South Africa CEO, Busisiwe Mavuso said the promises made at the summit are still valid and said,"markets respond to certainty and the lack thereof is problematic". Mavuso stated pledges are a good sign as there is still an investment in the economy but the background issues of energy instability and sluggish growth contribute to how businesses react individually.